						<summary>

						<p>Side-slab of a dolmen (No. 2) in front of the deserted Vishṇu temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 10th century.</p>						

						<p>This worn out record registers the death of Puḷiyamma, the younger brother of Pṛithivirāma-seṭṭi, son of Balimurka-gavuṇḍa of Eḍeyūr, Dōramma and others in a battle. It mentions a Noḻaṁba and refers to Mārajavāḍi and to a gift of land.</p>						

						</summary>
